    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="76"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 493.11/513.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">MacMurray</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 19, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Foreign Office states that the customs receipts will not suffice to meet in
                    full the Boxer indemnity payments in addition to prior charges, and asks consent
                    to China’s awaiting conclusion of the war to make up deficiencies.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
